8:
*sigh* Looks like mother and father
are going to be late again.
9:
Maybe they're busy with work? Or
maybe they have other plans... Who
knows.
13: But at least you're still here, Aperio...
15:
It's past midnight now... The holidays
are officially over.
27:
Good work today, everybody! That's
a wrap for this year's holiday
giveaway!
30:
And that means we can get started
with the holiday party! Time to move
out to the bar!
33:
Sorry, but I'm afraid that I won't be
joining.
37:
Oh, do you already have plans?
Understandable—it is the holidays,
after all...
40:
Not quite. Don't you remember? I
told you that I'm not a fan of this
season to begin with.
45:
Hold that thought for a second. It
says here that one child was
absent—that means we have a
leftover present.
49:
Yes, that happens from time to time.
Every year there's some kid who
can't make it for one reason or
another.
53:
But I wouldn't worry about it too
much! Somebody from the Guild will
deliver it at some point in the future!
57: ...And how long will that take, exactly?
66:
Do you have that kid's address? I'll
go drop it off myself.
69:
...But we don't even know if they'll be
home!
73: Well, there's only one way to find out.
76:
Holiday presents need to be
delivered during the holidays, right?
Otherwise it defeats the purpose.
81:
Apologies for the intrusion. We've
come to deliver you a present.
88:
I have a little something just for
you—a token of my love.
91:
Hurry up and get better, ok? That's
an order. Hehe.
97: Looks like the party's already over.
100: Yes... And so are the holidays.
103:
Ah, I forgot. I left my clothes back in
there—give me a second to go in
and grab them.
107:
Go ahead. I believe there are still
people inside, so the door shouldn't
be locked.
116:
Thanks for taking care of that last
present, Bianca!
120:
Looks like even Santa gets a present
this year—for all your hard work!
124: Huh? What's the meaning of all this?
127:
We saw how hard you worked back
there, so we wanted to return the
favor.
133:
Everyone chipped in to get
something special just for you!
138:
I am glad we could give this to you
before the holidays ended.
142: Is this all some sort of joke?
146:
Not at all! Everyone was saying that
this was the best way to surprise
you.
150:
Here, Bianca. I would like you to have
this.
154:
This gift is directly from me to you.
You said you liked books, right? I was
hoping this would be well-aligned
with your interests.
164:
I-is it?! I didn't realize... I merely
thought the illustrations would be to
your liking!
168:
Seems like there are things you still
need to learn about your master...
170:
...But I appreciate the effort. Thank
you.
173:
I suppose now I need to give my
cute pets a little something in return.
181:
I mean that it's far too soon to end
this party! How about it? Let's drink
until the sun comes up!
184:
Of course, you and Stella are more
than welcome to join in as well.
189:
Uh... Actually, we're both still not old
enough to drink...
192:
Oh come now, don't you want to see
how we adults celebrate the
holidays? Hehe. Nobody is going to
bed on my watch.
198:
B-Bianca! He just said they were
underage, didn't he?!
202:
Ahaha. Uptight as always. If those
two aren't coming, I suppose I'll have
to have my fill with just you.
205: I'll give you a night to remember.
210: H-hands off! Let go of me—
